Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
gen_vp(25.10)                                                    gen_vp(25.10)

Name
       gen_vp - The gen_vp command automatically generates the LEF file, which
       includes the via pillar rules and the via pillar cell association list

Syntax
       gen_vp

       [-help]

       [-allow_finger_outside_cell {0 1}]

       [-dont_gen_list <string>]

       [-em_config_file <string>]

       [-finger_pitch <string>]

       [-gen_list <string>]

       [-match_pattern <string>]

       [-max_cell_extension <string>]

       [-max_finger_quantity <string>]

       -output_association_file <string>

       -output_rule_lef_file <string>

       [-prefix <string>]

       [-process_node {N7 N7Plus N6 N5 N4 N3 N2 S5 S3 P1278 P1280}]

       [-specify_cut_class <string>]

       [-top_num_limit <string>]

       [-vp_bottom_layer <string>]

       [-vp_top_layers <string>]

       [-write_cut_class {0 1}]

       The gen_vp command automatically generates the LEF file, which includes
       the via pillar rules and the via pillar cell association list. It helps
       in  the  creation  of   DRC-free via pillar rules for different process
       nodes.

       Note: This command requires the timing library and the LEF files to  be
       pre-loaded in Innovus.

       The  gen_vp  command evaluates cell pin lengths and cell widths/heights
       when creating via pillars and filters out unimplementable  via  pillars
       from  the  association  lists. The gen_vp command cannot handle complex
       cells that have multiple pins and cell OBS shapes.

Parameters
       -allow_finger_outside_cell {0 1}
              When set to 1, it allows 1 finger to be outside the cell if mul-
              tiple fingers cannot be created within the cell boundary.

              Default: 0

              Data_type: enum, optional

       -dont_gen_list <string>
              Specifies the file that contains the list of cells that  do  not
              generate via pillars.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each gen_vp parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command

              man gen_vp.

       -em_config_file <string>
              Specifies the name of the EM config file.  The  EM  config  file
              must follow EM syntax/format.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -finger_pitch <string>
              Specifies the pitch of each layer's finger.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -gen_list <string>
              Specifies the file that contains the list of cells that generate
              via pillars.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -match_pattern <string>
              Specifies the customized library cell match pattern to catch the
              footprint and driving strength.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -max_cell_extension <string>
              Specifies  the maximum extension pitch outside the cell boundary
              for via pillar fingers creation.

              Note: Specify the value by layer.

              Default: 1 for all layers

              Data_type: string, optional

       -max_finger_quantity <string>
              Specifies the maximum finger quantity by layer.

              Note: The value must be larger than or equal to 2.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -output_association_file <string>
              Specifies the name of the file used for generating standard mode
              via pillar association list.

              Data_type: string, required

       -output_rule_lef_file <string>
              Specifies the name of the file used for generating standard/rich
              mode combined via pillar rule LEF.

              Data_type: string, required

       -prefix <string>
              Specifies the prefix name to be applied to via pillars.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -process_node {N7 N7Plus N6 N5 N4 N3 N2 S5 S3 P1278 P1280}
              Specifies the library process node.  The  default  finger  pitch
              corresponds to the process node.

              Note:  You  can  change the finger pitch using the -finger_pitch
              parameter.

              Data_type: enum, optional

       -specify_cut_class <string>
              Specifies the cut class of each cut layer.

              For example, the following command sets the  cut  class  of  via
              VIA1 as SINGLECUT:

              gen_vp -specify_cut_class {VIA1 SINGLECUT_A}

              Data_type: string, optional

       -top_num_limit <string>
              Specifies  the number of top largest rules to write out for each
              cell.

              Default: No limit

              Data_type: string, optional

       -vp_bottom_layer <string>
              Specifies the bottom layer of the created via pillars where pins
              are available on the specified layer.

              Default: M1

              Data_type: string, optional

       -vp_top_layers <string>
              Specifies the top layers of the created via pillars.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -write_cut_class {0 1}
              When enabled, the cut class is written in the vp file.

              Default: 0

              Data_type: enum, optional

Examples
              * The following command generates via pillars for a TSMC process
                node with a don't generate list:

                gen_vp   -output_association_file   vp_association.tcl   -out-
                put_rule_lef_file   vp_rule.lef -max_finger_quantity { M3 3 M4
                3 } -process_node N3  -vp_top_layers  {M5  M6}  -dont_gen_list
                dontGen.txt -finger_pitch {M5 2 M6 2}

              * The  following  command  generates via pillars with customized
                library and match pattern:

                cell name: <uln8_xor2t02p57>

                gen_vp   -output_association_file   vp_association.tcl   -out-
                put_rule_lef_file vp_rule.lef -gen_list Gen.txt -vp_top_layers
                M5     -finger_pitch    {M2    2    M3    2}    -match_pattern
                {(.*)(t)([0-9]+)(\D*)}

              * The following command generates via pillars up to high  layers
                and  not  bounded within cell boundary for specific cells such
                as clock buffers/inverters:

                gen_vp  -output_association_file   vp_associations.tcl   -out-
                put_rule_lef_file     vp_rule.lef     -gen_list    genList.txt
                -vp_top_layers  M11  -finger_pitch  {M8  3   M9   3   M10   3}
                -max_cell_extension  {M8  2  M9  3  M10  3} -allow_finger_out-
                side_cell 1

              * The following command  generates  via  pillars  for  an  Intel
                process node:

                gen_vp  -process_node  P1278  -output_association_file  vp.tcl
                -output_rule_lef_file     vp.lef     -match_pattern     "(\[a-
                z0-9\]{9})(\[a-z0-9\]{4})(\[0-9\]{2})(\[a-z0-9\]+)"
                -vp_top_layers {m3 m4 m5}

              * The  following  command  generates  via  pillars for a Samsung
                process node:

                gen_vp  -output_association_file   vp_associations.tcl   -out-
                put_rule_lef_file   vp_rule.lef   -process_node   S5  -vp_bot-
                tom_layer M1 -vp_top_layers  D1  -allow_finger_outside_cell  1
                -match_pattern {(.*)(B)(.*)}

